            "body": "Thanks for the quick response!\n\n> First question: _why_ are you calling `syntax enable` (which is a command, not an option, with _intended_ side effects) at all?\n\nI've had it like this for years, since I started using vim, and I just never changed it. I suppose with nvim enabling syntax highlighting by default, I probably could just get rid of it.\n\nMostly I was confused because on v0.11 everything worked as I expected with this same config. With the upgrade to v0.12 I started seeing different behavior.\n",
