            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I have a similiar problem: \n\nWhen I open a markdown-file in nvim the syntax-highlighting is broken. Asterisk are red instead of blue, headlines are green, but always thick etc.\n\nI tried to debug this with a mwe:\n```\nset termguicolors\n\ncall plug#begin()\nPlug 'gruvbox-community/gruvbox'\ncall plug#end()\n\nset nocompatible\nfiletype plugin on\nfiletype indent on\nfiletype on\n\ncolorscheme gruvbox\n```\nOutput `:scriptnames`\n```\n 1: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/ftplugin.vim\n  2: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/indent.vim\n  3: /etc/xdg/nvim/sysinit.vim\n  4: /usr/share/nvim/archlinux.lua\n  5: ~/.dotfiles/nvim/.config/nvim/init.vim\n  6: ~/.dotfiles/nvim/.local/share/nvim/site/autoload/plug.vim\n  7: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/filetype.lua\n  8: /usr/share/vim/vimfiles/ftdetect/PKGBUILD.vim\n  9: /usr/share/vim/vimfiles/ftdetect/SRCINFO.vim\n 10: /usr/share/vim/vimfiles/ftdetect/augeas.vim\n 11: /usr/share/vim/vimfiles/ftdetect/espeakfiletype.vim\n 12: /usr/share/vim/vimfiles/ftdetect/lf.vim\n 13: /usr/share/vim/vimfiles/ftdetect/meson.vim\n 14: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/syntax/syntax.vim\n 15: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/syntax/synload.vim\n 16: ~/.dotfiles/nvim/.local/share/nvim/plugged/gruvbox/colors/gruvbox.vim\n 17: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/plugin/gzip.vim\n 18: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/plugin/matchit.vim\n 19: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/pack/dist/opt/matchit/plugin/matchit.vim\n 20: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/plugin/matchparen.vim\n 21: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/plugin/netrwPlugin.vim\n 22: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/pack/dist/opt/netrw/plugin/netrwPlugin.vim\n 23: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/plugin/rplugin.vim\n 24: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/plugin/tarPlugin.vim\n 25: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/plugin/tutor.vim\n 26: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/plugin/zipPlugin.vim\n 27: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/plugin/editorconfig.lua\n 28: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/plugin/man.lua\n 29: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/plugin/net.lua\n 30: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/plugin/osc52.lua\n 31: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/plugin/shada.lua\n 32: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/plugin/spellfile.lua\n 33: /usr/share/vim/vimfiles/plugin/fzf.vim\n 34: /usr/share/vim/vimfiles/plugin/redact_pass.vim\n```\nOutput `:echo &runtimepath`\n```\n/home/<USER>/.config/nvim,/home/<USER>/.local/share/nvim/plugged/gruvbox,/etc/xdg/nvim,/home/<USER>/.local/share/nvim/site,/usr/local/share/nvim/site,/usr/share/nvim/site,/usr/share/nvim/runtime,/usr/share/nvim/runtime/pack/dist/opt/netrw,/usr/share/nvim/runtime/pack/dist/opt/matchit,/usr/lib/nvim,/usr/share/nvim/site/after,/usr/local/share/nvim/site/after,/home/<USER>/.local/share/nvim/site/after,/etc/xdg/nvim/after,/home/<USER>/.config/nvim/after,/usr/share/vim/vimfiles,/usr/share/vim/vimfiles/after\n```\n\nit seems that since nvim-version 0.12 the syntax is not set correctly:\n\n`:set filetype?` shows `filetype=markdown`\n`:set syntax?` just shows `syntax=`\n\nTested with:\nnvim 0.12.2\ngruvbox-community/gruvbox\n\n\nOlder versions of nvim works as expected.\n\nHas anyone also this problem?\n\n",
